# Graphify — knowledge graph for iPix

**SSOT graph:** `graphify-out/graph.json` (repo root — CLI default).  
**Skill hub:** `.claude/skills/graphify/SKILL.md`  
**Docs:** [graphify.net](https://graphify.net/) · [Knowledge graphs for AI coding](https://graphify.net/knowledge-graph-for-ai-coding-assistants.html) · [GitHub](https://github.com/Graphify-Labs/graphify)

Graphify builds a **queryable knowledge graph** from code, docs, and schemas so agents traverse structure (`calls`, `imports`, `rationale_for`) instead of grepping raw files. On mixed corpora, queries cost ~**71× fewer tokens** than reading files directly ([Graphify docs](https://graphify.net/knowledge-graph-for-ai-coding-assistants.html)).

## Golden rules

| ✅ Do | ❌ Don't |
|-------|---------|
| Run **`graphify query`** before reading multi-file source | Grep-first on cross-module questions |
| Use **`graphify explain`** for a symbol before opening its file | Trust training-data API shapes without graph + file check |
| Use **`graphify path`** for "what connects A to B" | Use `docs/graphify/graphify-out/` — graph is at **repo root** |
| Rebuild after large moves: **`graphify update .`** | Run `graphify update docs/graphify/` (overwrites with docs-only subgraph) |
| Read **`GRAPH_REPORT.md`** for god nodes and surprising edges | Query a stale graph (>10 files newer than `graph.json`) |

## Install (verify)

```bash
graphify --version          # expect graphify 0.9.x via pipx/pip install graphifyy
graphify query "Mastra"     # smoke test — should return nodes
```

Optional Cursor skill copy: `graphify install --platform cursor`

## Mandatory workflow (before source reads)

```bash
# From repo root (or: cd "$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)")

# 1. Orient — scoped subgraph around your question
graphify query "<question>"

# 2. Symbol lookup — neighbors and provenance
graphify explain "<concept>"

# 3. Connection — shortest path (use specific node names from query/explain)
graphify path "<A>" "<B>"

# 4. Blast radius — what breaks if X changes
graphify affected "<node>"
```

**Only read raw files after graphify orients you**, or to edit specific lines you already identified.

### Path tips

- Vague labels (`CopilotKit`, `Mastra`) often **fail** — use names from `query`/`explain` (e.g. `getMastra()`, `app/src/mastra/index.ts`).
- Graph may note **pre-#1504 ID scheme** — rebuild with `graphify extract --force` for path-qualified IDs.

