## Rebuild & freshness

```bash
# Incremental update (repo root)
graphify update .

# Force full AST re-extract
graphify update . --force
# or: graphify extract --force

# App-only subgraph
cd app/src && graphify update .
```

**Stale gate:** if >10 tracked files are newer than `graphify-out/graph.json`, rebuild before querying.

Excludes: `.graphifyignore` at repo root (`github/`, `node_modules/`, vendored trees, etc.).

## When NOT to use graphify

- Single known file + line edit
- Simple literal grep (`rg 'exactSymbol'`)
- Secrets / `.env` inspection
- Graph missing or empty — run `graphify update .` first

## Graph health check

```bash
graphify diagnose multigraph
# expect: 0 missing_endpoint_edges, 0 dangling_endpoint_edges
```

## What the graph contains ([features](https://graphify.net/index.html#features))

- **God nodes** — high-degree hubs everything routes through
- **Surprising connections** — cross-file edges with plain-English _why_
- **Rationale nodes** — docstrings, `# WHY:` comments, design docs via `rationale_for`
- **Edge provenance** — `EXTRACTED` vs `INFERRED` vs `AMBIGUOUS` + confidence

